Awesome.  Am I right in understanding that LLVM IR should be LLVM IF or LLVM assembly? The generated code is most extremely simplistic.  An example would be:<p><pre><code>  A[12800]=A[0] * A[6400];
  A[12801]=A[1] * A[6480];
  A[12802]=A[12800] + A[12801];
  A[12803]=A[2] * A[6560];
  A[12804]=A[12802] + A[12803];
  A[12805]=A[3] * A[6640];
</code></pre>
Which would be very easy to deal with.  The only problem is that I sometimes call out to libraries for exp, log, sin, cos, etc.
